Rule: Individuals with higher education levels (Bachelors or Doctorate) are more likely to earn more than $50k compared to those with "Some-college" education.
Individuals who work more hours per week (e.g., 75 or 90 hours) are more likely to earn more than $50k compared to those who work 40 hours per week.
Individuals with a "White-Collar" occupation are more likely to earn more than $50k compared to those in "Blue-Collar" occupations, even if the hours worked per week are the same.
